From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hidekazu Kondo <hidekazu.kondo@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0900
Subject: fix: don't NOTREACHED in ShadowRealmGlobalScope UKM accessors

V8 attributes GC metrics events (V8MetricsRecorder::AddMainThreadEvent ->
GetUkmRecorderAndSourceId) to the context in which the collection was
triggered. When that context is a ShadowRealm - which Electron uses for
every service-worker preload realm - the resolved ExecutionContext is a
ShadowRealmGlobalScope, whose UkmRecorder()/UkmSourceID() overrides are
NOTREACHED(). A full GC attributed to the realm therefore traps the
renderer (EXC_BREAKPOINT); for extension service workers the restart
machinery turns this into a crash loop (electron/electron#52310).

The caller already handles a null recorder (v8_metrics.cc
GetUkmRecorderAndSourceId null-checks), so report "no UKM" instead of
trapping. ShadowRealms have no UKM source by design.

This should be upstreamed to Chromium.

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/shadow_realm/shadow_realm_global_scope.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/shadow_realm/shadow_realm_global_scope.cc
index c4cc043dc9bac54dd0876198ac54a6b8133c71b6..d308ab541662f7a3e9c059d902229ec6ced1ecbe 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/shadow_realm/shadow_realm_global_scope.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/shadow_realm/shadow_realm_global_scope.cc
@@ -121,11 +121,14 @@ bool ShadowRealmGlobalScope::IsIsolatedContext() const {
 }
 
 ukm::UkmRecorder* ShadowRealmGlobalScope::UkmRecorder() {
-  NOTREACHED();
+  // V8 GC metrics events can be attributed to a ShadowRealm context (e.g.
+  // Electron's service-worker preload realms). ShadowRealms have no UKM;
+  // callers null-check the recorder, so report "none" instead of trapping.
+  return nullptr;
 }
 
 ukm::SourceId ShadowRealmGlobalScope::UkmSourceID() const {
-  NOTREACHED();
+  return ukm::kInvalidSourceId;
 }
 
 ExecutionContextToken ShadowRealmGlobalScope::GetExecutionContextToken() const {
